  <description><![CDATA[<p>Park City started life as a silver mining boom town in the late 1800's. Nowadays, it's a lively ski resort offering no less than three ski areas on one pass. <strong>Park City Mountain Resort,</strong> where most visitors choose to stay, has extensive skiing for all grades and boasts three of the best terrain parks in the world for boarders. <strong>Deer Valley</strong> is quieter with fast lifts and few queues. Snowboarding is banned here! <strong>Canyons</strong> is one of the five biggest skis areas in the US and best suited to advanced and intermediate skiers. The town centre of Park City has been carefully restored and a huge choice of bars and restaurants line historic Main Street. Between January 22 and February 1 2015 Park City will again host the famous Sundance Film Festival. Perhaps a visit to Robert Redford's restaurant afterwards! <strong>Tip</strong> - the Three Resort Pass is not available locally and must be purchased from us before you go.</p>]]></description>
