  <generalInformation><![CDATA[<p><strong>Beginners skiing in Park City, Utah<br /></strong></p>
<p>Beginners will make quick progress in Park City Mountain Resort moving quickly up the mountain. There's a wonderful gentle run over 3 miles long back down the mountain which you should be able to manage after just a few lessons.</p>
<p><strong>Intermediates skiing in <strong>Park City, Utah</strong><br /></strong></p>
<p>Intermediates are spoilt for choice with a huge choice of (some say) fairly short cruising runs in Park City and you'll want to explore the superbly groomed runs Deer Valley and Canyons offer during your stay.</p>
<p><strong>Advanced skiing in <strong>Park City, Utah</strong><br /></strong></p>
<p>There are some fairly steep runs through the trees for advanced skiers in Canyons and McConkey's Bowl in Park City offers some pretty testing skiing including some narrow couloirs.</p>
<p><strong>Snowboarding in <strong>Park City, Utah</strong><br /></strong></p>
<p>Boarders will be in heaven in Park City Mountain Resort which has some of the best terrain parks in the world. Boarding is actually banned in Deer Valley but you'll be welcomed in Canyons where you'll find a mile-long natural half-pipe.</p>]]></generalInformation>
